A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Camille Russell Love; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Camille Russell Love has diligently served as the executive director of the City
3 of Atlanta Mayor's Office of Cultural Affairs since 1998, guiding the cultural and artistic
4 vision of the Chastain Arts Center and Gallery, the City's Public Art Program, Gallery 72,
5 Elevate, Contracts for Arts Services, the Cultural Experience Project, and the Atlanta Jazz
6 Festival; and
7 WHEREAS, under her leadership, the Atlanta Jazz Festival has remained one of the nation's
8 preeminent free jazz festivals, providing world-class cultural programming and enriching the
9 artistic landscape of Atlanta; and
10 WHEREAS, she has further served on the boards of the Metropolitan Atlanta Arts Fund,
11 APEX Museum, Piedmont Park Conservancy, and the National Black Arts Festival as well
12 as contributed to the Coca-Cola Scholars Foundation National Selection Committee and the
13 1996 Cultural Olympiad Committee; and
14 WHEREAS, throughout her career, she has received accolades from numerous local,
15 national, and international entities for her contributions to arts and culture, including the
