16 Inspired Cultural Excellence Award from Omega Media in 2002, the Community Impact
17 Award from Living the Dream in 2007, and the distinction of Chevalier of the Order of Arts
18 and Letters from the French Minister of Culture and Communication in 2017; and
19 WHEREAS, Camille Russell Love has served with honor and distinction, and her vision and
20 unyielding commitment to the arts will be sorely missed upon the occasion of her retirement;
21 and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
23 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 recognize and commend Camille Russell Love for her decades of leadership in the arts,
26 congratulate her on the occasion of her retirement, and extend best wishes for continued
27 success and happiness.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
29 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Camille Russell
30 Love.
